args: Daaang. Talk about some sweet digs.
Ah, hello! You must be Farren and\nLil' Barb.
I'm {player_name}, and it's a\npleasure. Grace told me all\nabout the pair of you.

It sounds like you've been through a lot.
Between being captured by the Syndicate
and all the awful things they put you
through... I can't imagine.
Yeah... Can't say they left me with\nany happy memories, that's for sure.
The people I met died one after another,\nand yet I somehow kept surviving...
I'm terribly sorry to hear that, Farren.
But you know what? That's exactly why\nI can't just sit around moping all day!
I've gotta do my best and keep pushing on\nfor all the people who can't anymore!
Nah. He's just too thickheaded to let\nanything drag 'im down too long.
Ha ha. Well, in any event, it's certainly\nbetter than being downcast.
This castle is a safe place. You don't need\nto worry about the Syndicate anymore, so\nplease, make yourself at home and relax.
You better believe I will! Thank you so\nmuch, {player_name}. You've\nmade me feel really welcome!
And there...we go. Phew. Doing the\nwashing has become quite the gargantuan\nundertaking around here, I must say.
Laundry day, huh?\nI'll help you dry it.
Ah, you're the newcomer, if I'm not\nmistaken. Your kind offer is appreciated,\nbut I can take care of it myself, thank you.
I heard that you've had quite the difficult\nexperience. Please, take it easy and rest.
I'm grateful for the consideration, but I'm\nnot the kinda guy who can just sit around.
I'd much prefer to be helpful to somebody!

So c'mon, let's get these slacks and shirts
or whatever nice and dr—WHOA, hold up!
You clothing an entire army here, or what?
We're gonna be here all day!

Hee hee. You're a curious young man. You
say something like that, but there you are
hanging the laundry with a smile on your
face.
I mean, what's not to smile about?\nI'm alive, y'know. And today's looking like\nanother peaceful day. Can't complain.
Being able to focus our attention on such\na mundane task is proof positive of peace.
'Kay, now that we're done with the wash,\nthe neeext thing I can do to help out is...
Hey, hold up. Sounds like there's some\nkinda fuss over there.
Got it! I'll knock some fiend heads off!
There are fiends out? C'mon, Lil' Barb.\nWe'll fight too!
Uhhh... You sure? Pretty sure we could\njust leave it to them...
The people here helped us out a lot.\nWe have to return the favor. C'mon!
Hey, don't go chargin' off alone!\n...Aaand the kid's gone.
Sheesh. Try lettin' a guy finish his\nsentence next time. Ah well. He's\nright—ain't cool to leave debts unpaid.
Let me in on the action,\n{player_name}!
Hey now, don't push it! You ain't even\ntrained in fightin' or anything, are ya?
It's all good! I've got this power of mine,\nafter—wait. Lil' Barb?
Gee, if only SOMEBODY had warned ya,\nFarren. You can't fight by yourself, y'know.
There you are! Took you long enough!
You're the one takin' off at full tilt. Got a\nlittle more appreciation for my value now?
Ya sure?! 'Cause it sure don't seem like it!
Come on, let's just do this already!
Farren... The way you look now—\nis that what the Syndicate did?!
Yup. This is the damnable power\nthose Syndicate pukes foisted on us.\nWyrmbinding.
Yeah, but as long as we have it,\nwe can PROTECT people!
And that's exactly how I've decided to\nuse it—not for myself, but for others!
All right. Let's do this thing,\nLil' Barb! Haaah!
...That takes care of that.\nYou were a big help, Farren.
For real. I kinda figured we'd have to\nprotect ya, what with you bein' a Syndicate\nvictim and all, but I guess I was wrong.
Yer still a greenhorn when it comes to\nthe WAY ya fight, but you got some guts,\nkiddo. Ranzal's seal of approval: granted!
And mine as well.\nWe're lucky to have you, Farren.
Awww. Heh. I promise I'll\nkeep giving everything I've got!
Yo, Farren! If you're gonna sleep,\nya could at least do it in a BED!
Sheesh. He's pushin' himself too far.\nPitchin' in with chores, rescuin' people\nin trouble, helpin' kill fiends...
Why's he so hell-bent on this selfless\nschtick?
